  "prompt": "What is the difference between Tarzan and Mowgli for a complete noob?",
  "response": "Here's a simple breakdown of the key differences between Tarzan and Mowgli:\n\nTarzan:\n- Created by Edgar Rice Burroughs in 1912\n- Raised by gorillas in Africa\n- A human who becomes a skilled jungle warrior\n- More adult-oriented stories\n- Usually depicted as physically strong and civilized\n- Becomes a bridge between human and animal worlds\n- Popularized by Disney animated film in 1999\n\nMowgli:\n- Created by Rudyard Kipling in 1894\n- Raised by wolves in India\n- A human child living among jungle animals\n- More child-focused stories (part of \"The Jungle Book\")\n- Generally portrayed as more wild and less civilized\n- Learns survival skills from animal \"family\"\n- Famously adapted by Disney in 1967 animated film\n\nSimilarities:\n- Both are humans raised by animals in the jungle\n- Both learn to survive and communicate with animals\n- Both become skilled hunters and jungle survivors\n- Both have been adapted multiple times in movies and media\n\nThe main difference is their origin, cultural context, and the specific nature of their relationship with their animal families.",
